text: I'm lvl 118. A few tips: Make sure you take a camera when first entering the building to ensure you get a picture of the ghost or anything else such as dirty water, bones, voodoo dolls, etc. Turn on all lights as you progress through the building, and ensure all lights are on that  lead to the ghost area from the entrance to reduce sanity loss (if the light switches are off when the breaker blows, you can turn them on as you move towards the breaker to make sure all those lights will be on when you turn the breaker back on). If the EMF reader goes to 3, there is a chance it will go to 5, if it's at 4 it will typically not go to 5. If you see a door move there is a good chance there will be fingerprints but there still may not be any. If there are closets or lockers in the building, remember where they are to hide in them if the ghost hunts. When using the spirit box, ask questions like "How old are you?", "Where are you?", and "What do you want?" to get quick answers (make sure you're in the dark to allow it to work). In case the ghost is a wraith, make sure you don't put salt in front of a sink to allow the ghost to turn on the water.... I learned the hard way, it was funny watching the ghost struggle to hunt on camera though trying to get past the salt. If possible, memorize the layout of the building from the map; make sure you know where the breaker box and exits are. You can use sound sensors to see what area the ghost is currently in, you can even use the triangulation method by diverging sensor coverage in the building to get accurate locations, just remember the sensors also pick up players as well. The parabolic microphone can be useful in large buildings, but from my experience it can be a bit difficult to use, it too like the sound sensors picks up the sound of doors and light switches that players interact with. That's all I can think of for now.
